The general procedure of the NMC-SMPIM is as follows.


Step 1: Determine the basic random variables and their stochastic characteristics in the system;

Step 2: Substitute the mean of the random variables into the equilibrium equation (14). Compute the inverse of the system stiffness matrix and obtain the solution as a base;

Step 3: Generate a set of random numbers of thebasic random variables (that is, one sample), and substitute them into the equilibrium equation (14);

Step 4: Use the Neumann expansion (19) to compute the approximate solution of the equilibrium equation (14);

Step 5: Repeat the (step3)-(step 4) until the number of samples reaches N, a pre-set size of the sample set.
